##  $ weekday     : Factor w/ 7 levels "Monday","Tuesday",..: 4 4 4 4 4 4 6 6 4 4 ...
##  $ year        : int  2018 2018 2018 2018 2018 2018 2018 2018 2018 2018 ...
```
:::


I've included functions in `ghreadme` for quickly making graphs to visualize your commits. 

#### Cumulative Line Plot

`cumulative_line_plot()` creates a line graph of the cumulative commits over time per repo: 


::: {.cell layout-align="center"}

```{.r .cell-code  code-fold="false"}
library(ggplot2)

cumulative_line_plot(
  stats$commits,
  repo = NULL,
  date_begin = "2023-01-01",
  date_end = "2026-06-01",
  top_n = 10,
  show_other = TRUE,
  title = "Cumulative Line Plot"
)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](index_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-5-1.png){fig-align='center' width=100%}
:::
:::



#### Calendar Heatmap Plot

`calendar_heatmap_plot()` creates a heatmap similar to the GitHub heatmap, and allows us to facet by year. 


::: {.cell layout-align="center"}

```{.r .cell-code  code-fold="false"}
calendar_heatmap_plot(
  stats$commits,
  repo = NULL,
  date_begin = "2023-01-01",
  date_end = "2026-06-01",
  title = "Calendar Heatmap",
  week_start = c("Sunday", "Monday"),
  low = "#ebedf0",
  high = "#216e39"
)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](index_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-6-1.png){fig-align='center' width=100%}
:::
:::



#### Punch Card Plot

`punchcard_plot()` lets you view the time of day your commits occur:


::: {.cell layout-align="center"}

```{.r .cell-code  code-fold="false"}
punchcard_plot(
  stats$commits,
  repo = NULL,
  date_begin = "2023-01-01",
  date_end = "2026-06-01",
  title = "Punchcard Plot",
  point_color = "#1f6feb"
)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](index_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-7-1.png){fig-align='center' width=100%}
:::
:::


